# Enable WSL Feature

1. Open PowerShell as Administrator
2. Run the following command to enable WSL and the Virtual Machine Platform feature:

dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart
dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart

# Install a Linux Distribution

1. Open Microsoft Store
2. Search for a Linux distribution - Ubuntu
3. Install
4. Setup user account with username and password

# Set WSL Version 

1. Open PowerShell as Administrator
2. Run the following command to set WSL version to 2:

wsl --set-version Ubuntu-20.04 2

# Ubuntu Linux environment setup complete
